casebody.data:
CINCINNATI BAR ASSN.
v.
MOORE 2014-1737 Supreme Court of Ohio. July 15, 2019

CASE ANNOUNCEMENT

DISCIPLINARY CASE

On the Board of Professional Conduct's request for reconsideration or clarification of remand order. Request for reconsideration denied. The board retains jurisdiction to consider misconduct committed during the period of licensure by an attorney who was later disbarred and therefore has the authority to hold a hearing and determine the factual issues raised by relator's second motion to hold respondent in contempt.
